{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give all on Carer's Allowance (or Clement) a work allowance on Universal Credit",
        "additional_details": "On Carer's Allowance you can only earn \u00a3128 a week without losing carers allowance.\r\n\r\nAlthough universal credit gives you a Carer's Element, Carer's Allowance is deducted \u00a31 for \u00a31. \r\n\r\nIf you work and have no dependent children on your claim your claim is reduced by 67p per \u00a31 in wages on top of carers allowance reduction.\r\n\r\nDue to the hours of caring these people do, most if not all carers struggle to work full time.\r\n\r\nA Universal Credit work allowance would support carers financially to work and care.",
        "background": "I would like Government to give any carers a work allowance on Universal Credit in line with having a dependant child or limited capacity to work.\r\n\r\nCurrent rate -\r\n\u00a3293 if got a housing element or housing costs\r\n\u00a3515 if for no housing costs",
